President Jacob Zuma has encouraged young people to emulate the spirit of the class of 1976 by contributing immensely to building a united, non-racial, non-sexist, safe and prosperous South Africa.Zuma said this head of the celebrations of National Youth Day.&#8220;The youth of 1976 was at the forefront of the liberation struggle, we further encourage our young people today to lead a struggle for radical socioeconomic transformation to ensure that everyone, in particular the youth, equally participate and benefit from the economy of the country,&#8221; said Zuma.President Zuma is expected to address the National Youth Day commemoration in Ventersdorp, in the North West province.Gompieno ke Letsatsi le le kgethegileng la Ba wa #YouthDay #BokoneBophirima that&#8217;s where we are pic.twitter.com/iftANrdmlG South African Gov (@GovernmentZA) June 16, 2017This year&#8217;s youth day is under the theme The Year of OR Tambo: Advancing Youth Economic Empowerment .June 16 commemorates the historic and courageous uprising by students in Soweto against the imposition of Afrikaans as a medium of instruction in black schools.This led to a tragic loss of life and injuries and was also a major turning point in the history of the liberation struggle in the country and in particular the participation of the youth.&#8220;This year s commemoration coincides with the centenary celebrations of the late former President of the governing party, the African National Congress and one of the key founding fathers of South Africa s liberation and constitutional democracy, Mr Reginald Oliver Tambo,&#8221; said Zuma.Zuma also stated that the National Youth Day provides an opportunity to take stock of the strides that government has made in promoting youth development.#YouthDay The youth are our future. We honour their courage and sacrifice. Nkosi Sikelel&#8217; iAfrika pic.twitter.com/Z1DaaJLv5r Yusuf Abramjee (@Abramjee) June 16, 2017Today we pay tribute to the class of 1976, who played a key role in our struggle let s preserve their legacy #YouthDay pic.twitter.com/hvqEvytOx9 South African Gov (@GovernmentZA) June 16, 2017&#8220;I pay tribute to the endless heroism of youth, you, the young lions. You, the young lions, have energised our entire struggle&#8221; #YouthDay pic.twitter.com/He6yQF22QP NelsonMandela (@NelsonMandela) June 16, 2017-TNA Reporter &nbsp;